&ldquo;Your tests are failing.&rdquo;
 This comment on a pull request is crushing. After all the effort you&rsquo;ve spent writing your code, adding new unit tests, and rebasing your changes to make each commit almost a work of art: how could your tests possibly be failing?
Begrudgingly, you sign into your CI server only to realize the failing tests have nothing to do with your code. You think, &ldquo;Hmm, maybe the code is more coupled than I expected.
